Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me compile my findings into a comprehensive report:

## Comprehensive Analysis: User Mappings Consumption Across Frontend

I've thoroughly explored the codebase and discovered a consistent pattern for how user mappings are fetched, transformed, and passed to child components. Here's the complete picture:

### 1. Fetch Pattern - All 8 Pages Use Identical Query

All pages fetch mappings via:
```typescript
const { data: userMappings } = useAnalyticsQuery(
  orpc.analytics.users.mappings.queryOptions({ input: { days: 30 } })
);
```

**Pages fetching:**
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/tunis-v1/apps/web/src/pages/dashboard/DevelopersListPage.tsx` (line 46)
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/tunis-v1/apps/web/src/pages/dashboard/DeveloperDetailPage.tsx` (line 99)
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/tunis-v1/apps/web/src/pages/dashboard/SessionsListPage.tsx` (line 83)
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/tunis-v1/apps/web/src/pages/dashboard/ProjectDetailPage.tsx` (line 62)
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/tunis-v1/apps/web/src/pages/dashboard/ROIPage.tsx` (line 66)
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/tunis-v1/apps/web/src/pages/dashboard/LearningsPage.tsx` (line 47)
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/tunis-v1/apps/web/src/pages/dashboard/ErrorsPage.tsx` (line 49)
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/tunis-v1/apps/web/src/components/analytics/Breadcrumb.tsx` (line 28, with optional `enabled` flag)

All use `useAnalyticsQuery` wrapper which adds org-scoped queryKey at `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/tunis-v1/apps/web/src/hooks/useAnalyticsQuery.ts` lines 8-16.

### 2. Data Structure: Inconsistent Transformation Patterns

The API returns: `UserMapping[] = { user_id: string, username: string }[]`

**Pattern A - Map → Record (DevelopersListPage, SessionsListPage, LearningsPage, ErrorsPage):**
```typescript
// Lines 50-60 in DevelopersListPage.tsx
const userMap = useMemo(() => {
  const map = new Map<string, string>();
  if (userMappings) {
    for (const m of userMappings) {
      map.set(m.user_id, m.username);
    }
  }
  return map;
}, [userMappings]);

const userMapRecord = useMemo(() => Object.fromEntries(userMap), [userMap]);
```

**Pattern B - Direct Record (DeveloperDetailPage, ProjectDetailPage, ROIPage):**
```typescript
// Lines 103-111 in DeveloperDetailPage.tsx
const userMapRecord = useMemo(() => {
  const record: Record<string, string> = {};
  if (userMappings) {
    for (const m of userMappings) {
      record[m.user_id] = m.username;
    }
  }
  return record;
}, [userMappings]);
```

**Pattern C - Map Only (LearningsPage):**
```typescript
// Lines 51-59 in LearningsPage.tsx
const userMap = useMemo(() => {
  const map = new Map<string, string>();
  if (userMappings) {
    for (const m of userMappings) {
      map.set(m.user_id, m.username);
    }
  }
  return map;
}, [userMappings]);
// Then passes Map to children, converts to Record only when needed
```

**Pattern D - Direct Record (Breadcrumb):**
```typescript
// Lines 33-41 in Breadcrumb.tsx
const userMap = useMemo(() => {
  const record: Record<string, string> = {};
  if (userMappings) {
    for (const m of userMappings) {
      record[m.user_id] = m.username;
    }
  }
  return record;
}, [userMappings]);
```

### 3. Child Components - Their Prop Expectations

**DeveloperTrendChart.tsx (lines 18-21):**
```typescript
interface DeveloperTrendChartProps {
  data: DeveloperTrendDataPoint[];
  userMap: Map<string, string>;  // Map type
}
```
- Receives `userMap` as `Map<string, string>`
- Uses `userMap.get(userId)` to look up usernames (line 105)

**DimensionAnalysisChart.tsx (lines 27-34):**
```typescript
interface DimensionAnalysisChartProps {
  data: DimensionAnalysisDataPoint[];
  dimension: string;
  metric: string;
  split_by?: string;
  showPercentage?: boolean;
  userMap?: Map<string, string>;  // Map type, optional
}
```
- Receives optional `Map<string, string>`
- Converts to Record when needed: `Object.fromEntries(userMap || new Map())` (line 88)

**LearningsTrendChart.tsx (lines 22-27):**
```typescript
interface LearningsTrendChartProps {
  data: Record<string, string | number>[];
  splitBy: "user_id" | "repository";
  onSplitByChange: (splitBy: "user_id" | "repository") => void;
  userMap?: Map<string, string>;  // Map type, optional
}
```
- Receives optional `Map<string, string>`
- Uses `userMap.get(key)` when splitBy is "user_id" (line 104)

**ErrorTrendChart.tsx (lines 24-39):**
```typescript
interface ErrorTrendChartProps {
